<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-24T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-24T12:36:00-05:00" n="402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 814.01B</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Leavell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-24T11:00:00-06:36">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 25, 11.41
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Guatemalan Government offers to our influential American citizen,
                                    <persName>Daniel B. Hodgsdon</persName>, long-time resident of
                                Guatemala, the position of custodian of alien properties, and he has
                                asked my advice. Would the Department approve my advising him to
                                accept? The appointment would be most desirable. Please advise as
                                soon as you can.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>